**Describe your issue**

I'm adding tailwind to an existing project which uses vanilla css for components and imports antd v3 .less files. To workaround existing styles overriding tailwind, I'm importing tailwind without layer directive and adding `important` to utilities: 

```
@import "tailwindcss/theme.css";
@import "tailwindcss/preflight.css";
@import "tailwindcss/utilities.css" important;
```

This results in custom properties being generated with !important which makes them invalid, eg:

```
.leading-6 {
  --tw-leading: calc(var(--spacing) * 6)!important;
  line-height: calc(var(--spacing) * 6)!important;
}
```

